<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,828,1933]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,828,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Rosa &amp; Xu" authorityName="Rosa &amp; Xu" box="[285,565,828,853]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Istiochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[285,414,828,853]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Istiochrysis</emphasis>
Rosa &amp; Xu
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[581,691,828,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[581,691,828,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to the Nearctic and Neotropical genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Kimsey &amp; Bohart, 1981" authorityName="Kimsey &amp; Bohart" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Caenochrysis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1284,1436,828,853]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Caenochrysis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kimsey" box="[151,444,863,888]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" refString="Kimsey, L. S. &amp; Bohart, R. M. (1981 ['' 1980 '']) A synopsis of the chrysidid genera of Neotropical America. Psyche, 87, 75 - 91. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1155 / 1980 / 21857" type="journal article" year="1981">
Kimsey &amp; Bohart, 
<number box="[386,444,864,888]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and the Palaearctic and Oriental genera 
<taxonomicName authority="Bischoff, 1913" authorityName="Bischoff" authorityYear="1913" box="[952,1255,863,888]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[952,1067,863,888]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Chrysidea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bischoff" box="[1082,1255,863,888]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" refString="Bischoff, H. (1913) Hymenoptera. Fam. Chrysididae. In: Wytsman, P. (Ed.), Genera insectorum. Fascicule 151. Bruxelles, L." type="journal volume" year="1913">
Bischoff, 
<number box="[1199,1255,864,888]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="1913.0">1913</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lichtenstein, 1876" authorityName="Lichtenstein" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Trichrysis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1324,1436,863,888]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Trichrysis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lichtenstein" box="[151,365,900,925]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" refString="Lichtenstein, J. (1876) Note sur le genre Chrysis. Petites nouvelles entomologiques, 145, 1 - 27." type="journal article" year="1876">
<collectingCountry box="[151,293,900,925]" name="Liechtenstein" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Lichtenstein</collectingCountry>
, 
<number box="[306,365,900,925]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="1876.0">1876</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, this new genus can be separated from 
<taxonomicName box="[942,1094,900,925]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Caenochrysis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[942,1094,900,925]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Caenochrysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1111,1226,900,925]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1111,1226,900,925]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Chrysidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1286,1398,900,925]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Trichrysis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1286,1398,900,925]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Trichrysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by male genitalia with extended longitudinal crest on aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[845,965,935,960]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 A – 1 F" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1354,1376]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,195,1330]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1330]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 A – 1 F. Genitalia. A – C. Istiochrysis ziliolii sp. nov., A, dorsal view; B, dorso-lateral view; C, lateral view; D. Trichrysis cyanea (Linnaeus), dorsal view; E. Chrysidea pumila (Klug), dorsal view; F. Caenochrysis doriae (Gribodo), dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263663/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Figs 
<number box="[903,913,936,960]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="1.0">1</number>
A– 
<number box="[955,965,936,960]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C); apex of aedeagus enlarged and folded laterally (
<figureCitation box="[262,386,972,997]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 A – 1 F" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1354,1376]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,195,1330]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1330]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 A – 1 F. Genitalia. A – C. Istiochrysis ziliolii sp. nov., A, dorsal view; B, dorso-lateral view; C, lateral view; D. Trichrysis cyanea (Linnaeus), dorsal view; E. Chrysidea pumila (Klug), dorsal view; F. Caenochrysis doriae (Gribodo), dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263663/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Figs 
<number box="[323,333,972,996]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="1.0">1</number>
A, 
<number box="[375,386,972,996]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B) (not enlarged in the other genera and tapering in 
<taxonomicName box="[1014,1167,972,997]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Caenochrysis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1014,1167,972,997]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Caenochrysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); facial fovea between antennal socket and lower margin of eye hardly visible and shallowly depressed and finely punctate (
<figureCitation box="[1288,1409,1007,1032]" captionStart="FIGURE 2 A – 2 D" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1122,1144]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,195,1100]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[188,1398,195,1100]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2 A – 2 D. Head of Istiochrysis gen. nov. A. Head, frontal view, arrow pointing to the shallow micropunctate and densely setose depression; B. Detail of the depression between clypeus and lower margin of eye by SEM; C. Metanotum with raised triangular median area, which is shallowly concave medially; D. Detail of the raised median area on metanotum by SEM." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263664/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Figs 
<number box="[1346,1360,1008,1032]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="2.0">2</number>
A, 
<number box="[1394,1409,1008,1032]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
B) (usually deeply depressed in 
<taxonomicName box="[479,631,1044,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Caenochrysis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[479,631,1044,1069]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Caenochrysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); pronotum without sublateral carina (
<figureCitation box="[1067,1156,1044,1069]" captionStart="FIGURE 3 A – 3 D. A" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1604,1626]" captionTargetBox="[150,1426,1269,1582]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,1255,1583]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3 A – 3 D. A. Fore wing of Istiochrysis gen. nov.. B. S 2 black spots of Istiochrysis gen. nov.; C. S 2 black spots of Trichrysis Lichtenstein; D. S 2 black spots of Caenochrysis Bohart &amp; Kimsey or Chrysidea Bischoff." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263665/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Fig. 
<number box="[1120,1133,1044,1068]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="3.0">3</number>
A
</figureCitation>
) (usually with sublateral carina in 
<taxonomicName box="[257,368,1079,1104]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Trichrysis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[257,368,1079,1104]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Trichrysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); fore wing discoidal cell with thin and completely sclerotised outer vein (faint in 
<taxonomicName box="[1304,1419,1079,1104]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1304,1419,1079,1104]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Chrysidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); apex of T 
<number box="[263,276,1116,1140]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="3.0">3</number>
without teeth (laterally dentate and medially undulate in 
<taxonomicName box="[934,1049,1116,1141]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[934,1049,1116,1141]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Chrysidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, tridentate in 
<taxonomicName box="[1210,1322,1116,1141]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Trichrysis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1210,1322,1116,1141]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Trichrysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); S 
<number box="[1362,1377,1116,1140]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="2.0">2</number>
with large, subrectangular, black spots extending to lateral margins (
<figureCitation box="[879,947,1151,1176]" captionStart="FIGURE 3 A – 3 D. A" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1604,1626]" captionTargetBox="[150,1426,1269,1582]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,1255,1583]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3 A – 3 D. A. Fore wing of Istiochrysis gen. nov.. B. S 2 black spots of Istiochrysis gen. nov.; C. S 2 black spots of Trichrysis Lichtenstein; D. S 2 black spots of Caenochrysis Bohart &amp; Kimsey or Chrysidea Bischoff." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263665/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Fig. 
<number box="[933,947,1152,1176]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B), somehow similar to those in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Linsenmaier, 1968" authorityName="Linsenmaier" authorityYear="1968" box="[151,536,1188,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Praestochrysis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,317,1188,1213]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Praestochrysis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier" box="[325,536,1188,1213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" refString="Linsenmaier, W. (1968) Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera). Zweiter Nachtrag. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 41 (1 - 4), 1 - 144." type="journal article" year="1968">
Linsenmaier, 
<number box="[480,536,1188,1213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="1968.0">1968</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(small, suboval, not extending to lateral margins in 
<taxonomicName box="[1132,1284,1188,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Caenochrysis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1132,1284,1188,1213]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Caenochrysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; suboval and separated in 
<taxonomicName box="[293,408,1223,1248]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[293,408,1223,1248]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Chrysidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[424,491,1223,1248]" captionStart="FIGURE 3 A – 3 D. A" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1604,1626]" captionTargetBox="[150,1426,1269,1582]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,1255,1583]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3 A – 3 D. A. Fore wing of Istiochrysis gen. nov.. B. S 2 black spots of Istiochrysis gen. nov.; C. S 2 black spots of Trichrysis Lichtenstein; D. S 2 black spots of Caenochrysis Bohart &amp; Kimsey or Chrysidea Bischoff." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263665/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Fig. 
<number box="[477,491,1224,1248]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
D), subtriangular and medially fused or nearly so in 
<taxonomicName box="[1082,1194,1223,1248]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Trichrysis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1082,1194,1223,1248]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Trichrysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1209,1275,1223,1248]" captionStart="FIGURE 3 A – 3 D. A" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1604,1626]" captionTargetBox="[150,1426,1269,1582]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,1255,1583]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3 A – 3 D. A. Fore wing of Istiochrysis gen. nov.. B. S 2 black spots of Istiochrysis gen. nov.; C. S 2 black spots of Trichrysis Lichtenstein; D. S 2 black spots of Caenochrysis Bohart &amp; Kimsey or Chrysidea Bischoff." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263665/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Fig. 
<number box="[1262,1275,1224,1248]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
C)) (
<bibRefCitation author="Bohart" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" refString="Bohart, R. M. &amp; Kimsey, L. S. (1982) A synopsis of the Chrysididae in America North of Mexico. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 33, 1 - 266." type="journal article" year="1982">
Bohart &amp; Kimsey 
<number box="[245,305,1260,1284]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="1982.0">1982</number>
</bibRefCitation>
