<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="592" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,828,1933]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1295,1320]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[356,414,1295,1320]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Male</emphasis>
. Head broader than high. Scapal basin with shallow depression on each side between antennal socket and lower margin of eye; depression visible only under certain angle (
<figureCitation box="[1153,1280,1332,1357]" captionStart="FIGURE 2 A – 2 D" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1122,1144]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,195,1100]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[188,1398,195,1100]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2 A – 2 D. Head of Istiochrysis gen. nov. A. Head, frontal view, arrow pointing to the shallow micropunctate and densely setose depression; B. Detail of the depression between clypeus and lower margin of eye by SEM; C. Metanotum with raised triangular median area, which is shallowly concave medially; D. Detail of the raised median area on metanotum by SEM." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263664/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Figs 
<number box="[1212,1226,1332,1356]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="2.0">2</number>
A, 
<number box="[1264,1280,1332,1356]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
B); bottom of depression filled with micro-punctures and densely setose. Scapal basin topped by TFC (
<figureCitation box="[1140,1233,1367,1392]" captionStart="FIGURE 2 A – 2 D" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1122,1144]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,195,1100]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[188,1398,195,1100]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2 A – 2 D. Head of Istiochrysis gen. nov. A. Head, frontal view, arrow pointing to the shallow micropunctate and densely setose depression; B. Detail of the depression between clypeus and lower margin of eye by SEM; C. Metanotum with raised triangular median area, which is shallowly concave medially; D. Detail of the raised median area on metanotum by SEM." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263664/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Figs 
<number box="[1196,1210,1368,1392]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="2.0">2</number>
A
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1244,1260,1368,1392]" captionStart="FIGURE 4 A – 4 F" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1842,1864]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,459,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[188,1398,459,1820]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4 A – 4 F. Istiochrysis ziliolii sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Head, frontal view; C. Mesosoma, dorsal view, arrow pointing to the metanotal concave medial area; D. Mesopleuron, lateral view; E. Metasoma, dorsal view; F. T 3, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
<number box="[1244,1260,1368,1392]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
B); scapal basin with white setae, especially along lateral sides (
<figureCitation box="[703,796,1404,1429]" captionStart="FIGURE 2 A – 2 D" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1122,1144]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,195,1100]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[188,1398,195,1100]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2 A – 2 D. Head of Istiochrysis gen. nov. A. Head, frontal view, arrow pointing to the shallow micropunctate and densely setose depression; B. Detail of the depression between clypeus and lower margin of eye by SEM; C. Metanotum with raised triangular median area, which is shallowly concave medially; D. Detail of the raised median area on metanotum by SEM." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263664/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Fig. 
<number box="[758,773,1404,1428]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="2.0">2</number>
A
</figureCitation>
). F 
<number box="[837,847,1404,1428]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="1.0">1</number>
l/w&gt; 
<number box="[913,926,1404,1429]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="3.0">3</number>
; MS= 
<number box="[1001,1010,1404,1428]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="1.0">1</number>
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" box="[1020,1089,1404,1428]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" name="University of Modena and Reggio Emilia, Department of Biology" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">MOD</collectionCode>
. Genal carina developed from gena to mandible. Subgenal area well defined. Median ocellus not lidded. Vertex without posterior depression beneath posterior ocellus. Mandible unidentate. Pronotum nearly as long as mesoscutellum with deep lateral depression, without sublateral carina. Mesopleuron with large episternal sulcus and scrobal sulcus (
<figureCitation box="[1277,1345,1511,1536]" captionStart="FIGURE 4 A – 4 F" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1842,1864]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,459,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[188,1398,459,1820]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4 A – 4 F. Istiochrysis ziliolii sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Head, frontal view; C. Mesosoma, dorsal view, arrow pointing to the metanotal concave medial area; D. Mesopleuron, lateral view; E. Metasoma, dorsal view; F. T 3, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Fig. 
<number box="[1330,1345,1512,1536]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
D); area between episternal sulcus and scrobal sulcus large and subtriangular. Metanotum with raised median area. Fore wing with thin but completely sclerotized outer veins of discoidal cell (
<figureCitation box="[961,1052,1583,1608]" captionStart="FIGURE 3 A – 3 D. A" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1604,1626]" captionTargetBox="[150,1426,1269,1582]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,1255,1583]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3 A – 3 D. A. Fore wing of Istiochrysis gen. nov.. B. S 2 black spots of Istiochrysis gen. nov.; C. S 2 black spots of Trichrysis Lichtenstein; D. S 2 black spots of Caenochrysis Bohart &amp; Kimsey or Chrysidea Bischoff." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263665/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Fig. 
<number box="[1015,1029,1584,1608]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="3.0">3</number>
A
</figureCitation>
). T 
<number box="[1091,1105,1584,1608]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="2.0">2</number>
and T 
<number box="[1180,1192,1584,1608]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="3.0">3</number>
with shallow median longitudinal carinae (
<figureCitation box="[390,458,1620,1645]" captionStart="FIGURE 4 A – 4 F" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1842,1864]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,459,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[188,1398,459,1820]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4 A – 4 F. Istiochrysis ziliolii sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Head, frontal view; C. Mesosoma, dorsal view, arrow pointing to the metanotal concave medial area; D. Mesopleuron, lateral view; E. Metasoma, dorsal view; F. T 3, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Fig. 
<number box="[443,458,1620,1644]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
E). Apex of T 
<number box="[615,628,1620,1644]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="3.0">3</number>
without teeth, but with shallow concavity, thus appearing bilobate (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4 A – 4 F" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1842,1864]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,459,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[188,1398,459,1820]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4 A – 4 F. Istiochrysis ziliolii sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Head, frontal view; C. Mesosoma, dorsal view, arrow pointing to the metanotal concave medial area; D. Mesopleuron, lateral view; E. Metasoma, dorsal view; F. T 3, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,166,1656,1680]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
F); pit row well developed with enlarged and partly fused pits (
<figureCitation box="[879,947,1655,1680]" captionStart="FIGURE 4 A – 4 F" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1842,1864]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,459,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[188,1398,459,1820]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4 A – 4 F. Istiochrysis ziliolii sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Head, frontal view; C. Mesosoma, dorsal view, arrow pointing to the metanotal concave medial area; D. Mesopleuron, lateral view; E. Metasoma, dorsal view; F. T 3, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Fig. 
<number box="[932,947,1656,1680]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
F). Black spots on S 
<number box="[1174,1189,1656,1680]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="2.0">2</number>
elongate, fused along lateral margins (
<figureCitation box="[333,399,1692,1717]" captionStart="FIGURE 3 A – 3 D. A" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1604,1626]" captionTargetBox="[150,1426,1269,1582]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,1255,1583]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3 A – 3 D. A. Fore wing of Istiochrysis gen. nov.. B. S 2 black spots of Istiochrysis gen. nov.; C. S 2 black spots of Trichrysis Lichtenstein; D. S 2 black spots of Caenochrysis Bohart &amp; Kimsey or Chrysidea Bischoff." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263665/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Fig. 
<number box="[386,399,1692,1716]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B) and distinctly separated mesally. Male genitalia with gonostyle of gonocoxa elongate and slender, aedeagus with enlarge longitudinal crest, well visible in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1022,1085,1727,1752]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 A – 1 F" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1354,1376]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,195,1330]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1330]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 A – 1 F. Genitalia. A – C. Istiochrysis ziliolii sp. nov., A, dorsal view; B, dorso-lateral view; C, lateral view; D. Trichrysis cyanea (Linnaeus), dorsal view; E. Chrysidea pumila (Klug), dorsal view; F. Caenochrysis doriae (Gribodo), dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263663/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Fig. 
<number box="[1074,1085,1728,1752]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C).
</paragraph>
