<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="592" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,828,1933]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1871,1896]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Etymology.</emphasis>
From Greek noun 
<emphasis box="[547,609,1873,1896]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">istion</emphasis>
(= sail), referring to the unique subsidiary structure longitudinally placed on aedeagus, looking like a sail in lateral view. The gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
